biography.bio: Darryl Kinsella was born in Dublin. After studying at the prestigious Gaiety School of Acting he began his professional career on stage appearing in classical plays including "Hamlet", "Macbeth" and "A Midsummers Nights Dream" as well as contemporary productions including "Sleeping Around", "Madame Melville" and "Amadeus".In 2008 he made his film debut in Irish comedy "Situations Vacant". In recent years Darryl has worked primarily on television in shows such as "The Roaring Twenties" (RTE) "Pubworld" (RTE) "Mariana" (RTE) and "Camelot" (Starz/BBC). Most recently Darryl has had lead roles in psychological horror "Demon Within" (2013) "Maisie" (2013) and the acclaimed "Self Assembly" (2014) as well as appearing in high profile advertising campaigns for Kilbeggan Whiskey and AIG Insurance.
biography.name: Darryl Kinsella
